cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite the paper (preferred) or this repository."
title: "Mechanically-Gated Agent Safety: Byte-Confirmed, Model-Indexed Dissociations of Monitorability and Credential Leakage in LLM Code-Agents"
abstract: >-
  An executed, byte-confirmed study of when OS-level runtime monitoring can see an
  LLM code-agent exfiltrate a secret. We find a "cognitive air-gap" — taint tracking
  is structurally blind to a secret the agent carries through its context and re-types
  as a literal — and that whether this happens is a model-indexed coding idiom, so
  monitorability is a property of the model, not just the monitor.
